Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on device-to-device communication and cellular hybrid network, which are both related to networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of sparse code multiple access (SCMA) and compares it with orthogonal frequency-division multiple access (OFDMA) in terms of area spectral efficiency (ASE), which are both related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper develops a stochastic geometry-based framework to model and analyze SCMA, which is related to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions resource allocation in the overlaid mode, which may involve multimedia applications. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - Although less likely, the paper may have implications for the societal impact of wireless networks and their capacity to support massive device connectivity.
